[2026-03-18T17:35:15.853Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019H9AKvJpr2AwrJL9WNJXAn","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. **Database Layer Architecture**\n\nThe database layer has been refactored from a single monolithic database (`packages/orchestrator/src/db.ts` - now deleted) to a **multi-tenant per-database architecture** with the following structure:\n\n**File:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/`\n\nKey components:\n- `index.ts` - Barrel export (consolidates all database modules)\n- `schema.ts` - Table definitions and database initialization\n- `_helpers.ts` - Prepared statement caching and row mappers\n- `executions.ts` - Execution CRUD operations\n- `events.ts` - Event and subscription management\n- `triggers.ts` - Trigger definitions and scheduling\n- `personas.ts` - Persona management\n- `tools.ts` - Tool definitions\n- `credentials.ts` - Credential storage\n- `inferenceProfiles.ts` - Model/provider profiles\n\n**Database Structure:**\n- **System database** (`system.db`): Contains tenant registry and system-wide metrics\n- **Per-tenant databases** (`tenants/{hash}.db`): Individual SQLite databases for each project/tenant\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Daily Metrics Table Structure**\n\n**Location:** `packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` (lines 53-68)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS daily_metrics (\n  date TEXT NOT NULL,\n  total_executions INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  completed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  failed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  total_cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  total_duration_ms INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  PRIMARY KEY (date)\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS retention_watermark (\n  key TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT 'executions',\n  last_rowid INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\n);\n```\n\n**System-level equivalent** (`system_daily_metrics` in `system.db`):\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS system_daily_metrics (\n  date TEXT NOT NULL,\n  total_executions INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  completed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  failed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  total_cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  total_duration_ms INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  tenant_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  aggregated_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  PRIMARY KEY (date)\n);\n```\n\nEach tenant's database has its own `daily_metrics` table, which gets aggregated into `system_daily_metrics` daily.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **updateExecution() Function**\n\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/executions.ts` (lines 92-120)\n\n```typescript\nexport function updateExecution(db: Database.Database, id: string, updates: Record<string, unknown>): void {\n  const fields: string[] = [];\n  const values: unknown[] = [];\n\n  const columnMap: Record<string, string> = {\n    status: 'status',\n    outputData: 'output_data',\n    claudeSessionId: 'claude_session_id',\n    modelUsed: 'model_used',\n    inputTokens: 'input_tokens',\n    outputTokens: 'output_tokens',\n    costUsd: 'cost_usd',\n    errorMessage: 'error_message',\n    durationMs: 'duration_ms',\n    startedAt: 'started_at',\n    completedAt: 'completed_at',\n  };\n\n  for (const [key, col] of Object.entries(columnMap)) {\n    if (key in updates) {\n      fields.push(`${col} = ?`);\n      values.push(updates[key]);\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (fields.length === 0) return;\n  values.push(id);\n  stmt(db,`UPDATE persona_executions SET ${fields.join(', ')} WHERE id = ?`).run(...values);\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose:** Updates execution records dynamically based on a whitelist of allowed columns. It only updates fields that are explicitly provided in the `updates` object.\n\n**Used by:** `dispatcher.ts` to mark executions as:\n- `running` (lines 440-444)\n- `queued` (lines 184, 194, 235, 452)\n- `completed`/`failed` with full details (line 126)\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Retention and Purge Logic**\n\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts`\n\n**Key concepts:**\n\n1. **Daily wall-clock job** (lines 64-100):\n   - Runs once per UTC calendar day\n   - Uses `system_kv` table to persist last run date\n   - Triggered by 60-second polling check\n   - Yields event loop between operations\n\n2. **Three-step per-tenant retention** (lines 232-387):\n   \n   **Step 1: Batch Index Scan** (lines 246-263)\n   - Collects purgeable execution rowids in temp table `_ret_ids`\n   - Processes rows older than retention cutoff with status in ('completed', 'failed', 'cancelled')\n   - Batches collection to avoid holding write lock\n\n   **Step 2: Metrics Aggregation** (lines 269-317)\n   - Uses watermark-based deduplication (tracks `last_rowid`)\n   - Groups executions by `date(created_at)`\n   - Aggregates only never-before-counted rows\n   - Upserts into `daily_metrics` with additive updates:\n\n     ```sql\n     INSERT INTO daily_metrics (date, total_executions, completed, failed, total_cost_usd, total_duration_ms)\n     VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\n     ON CONFLICT(date) DO UPDATE SET\n       total_executions = total_executions + excluded.total_executions,\n       completed = completed + excluded.completed,\n       failed = failed + excluded.failed,\n       total_cost_usd = total_cost_usd + excluded.total_cost_usd,\n       total_duration_ms = total_duration_ms + excluded.total_duration_ms\n     ```\n\n   **Step 3: Deletion** (lines 319-346)\n   - Pre-purge safety check: refuses if deletion would exceed `EXEC_MAX_PURGE_FRACTION` (80%)\n   - Deletes in chunks of 5000 rows with event-loop yields\n\n3. **Event Purge** (lines 348-376):\n   - Deletes non-pending events older than retention cutoff\n   - Safety net: purges stuck events older than 7x retentionDays\n\n4. **System-wide Metrics Aggregation** (lines 150-230):\n   - Map-reduce: reads `daily_metrics` from all tenant databases\n   - Aggregates per-date totals across all tenants\n   - Writes to `system_daily_metrics` wholesale in single transaction\n   - Tracks `tenant_count` per date\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Table Registry (Metrizable Classification)**\n\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport const TABLE_REGISTRY: readonly TableRetentionSpec[] = [\n  {\n    lifecycle: 'metrizable',\n    table: 'persona_executions',\n    timestampColumn: 'created_at',\n    metrizableColumns: [\n      { column: 'cost_usd', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n      { column: 'duration_ms', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n      { column: 'input_tokens', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n      { column: 'output_tokens', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n    ],\n    aggregationTarget: 'daily_metrics',\n    maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n  },\n\n  {\n    lifecycle: 'ephemeral',\n    table: 'persona_events',\n    timestampColumn: 'created_at',\n    maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n  },\n  {\n    lifecycle: 'ephemeral',\n    table: 'audit_events',\n    timestampColumn: 'timestamp',\n    minRetentionDays: 90,\n    maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n  },\n];\n```\n\nThis is the **single source of truth** for which tables are metrizable vs ephemeral. Helper functions:\n- `getTableSpec(tableName)` - lookup by table name\n- `isMetrizable(spec)` - type guard\n- `isEphemeral(spec)` - type guard\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Tenant Database Manager**\n\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/tenantDbManager.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport class TenantDbManager {\n  private systemDb: Database.Database;\n  private tenantDbs = new Map<string, CachedDb>();\n  \n  // Layout:\n  // {dataDir}/system.db           — tenant registry\n  // {dataDir}/tenants/{hash}.db   — per-tenant data\n  \n  getTenantDb(projectId: string): Database.Database\n  listTenantIds(): string[]\n  forEachTenant(fn: (db: Database.Database, projectId: string) => void): void\n}\n```\n\nFeatures:\n- **Connection pooling** with idle eviction (10-minute timeout)\n- **Auto-registration** of new tenants in system.db\n- **Safe filenames** via SHA256 hashing of projectId\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Related Code Files**\n\n**Database Initialization:**\n- `schema.ts:initDb()` - Legacy single-db initialization (still used in migrations)\n- `schema.ts:initSystemDb()` - System database\n- `schema.ts:initTenantDb()` - Per-tenant database\n\n**Row Mapper Helpers** (`_helpers.ts`):\n- `stmt(db, sql)` - Prepared statement cache (WeakMap for GC)\n- `createRowMapper<T>(columnMap)` - Generic row mappers replacing per-entity boilerplate\n- `buildWhereClause()` - Dynamic WHERE clause builder\n- `mergeUpdate()` - Update with `updated_at` timestamp\n\n**Execution Schema** (`schema.ts:185-206`):\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_executions (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  trigger_id TEXT,\n  use_case_id TEXT,\n  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued' \n    CHECK(status IN ('queued','running','completed','failed','cancelled')),\n  input_data TEXT,\n  output_data TEXT,\n  claude_session_id TEXT,\n  model_used TEXT,\n  input_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  output_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  error_message TEXT,\n  duration_ms INTEGER,\n  retry_of_execution_id TEXT,\n  retry_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  started_at TEXT,\n  completed_at TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Insights\n\n1. **Metrics aggregation is watermark-based** to ensure idempotency even on crash/restart\n2. **Chunked deletion** with event-loop yields prevents starving concurrent operations\n3. **Additive aggregation** allows safely re-running if previous run partially completed\n4. **Safety caps** (maxPurgeFraction) prevent accidental mass deletion\n5. **Daily job** is wall-clock based (checks every 60s, runs once per UTC calendar day)\n6. **Per-tenant + system aggregation** allows both granular and system-wide metrics\n7. **Registry pattern** makes it easy to add new metrizable tables\n\nAll file paths are absolute from the project root."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a07ec8fbc6fe597bf (use SendMessage with to: 'a07ec8fbc6fe597bf' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 48128\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 74507</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6514e5c3-f34b-45a0-bfca-f77eb10eda6a","uuid":"744576c3-87f3-4c6d-b0d0-90c2606d23ee","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:35:15.773Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to understand:\n1. The current database layer - look at packages/orchestrator/src/db/ directory and the old packages/orchestrator/src/db.ts (deleted)\n2. How daily_metrics table is structured and used\n3. The updateExecution() function - where it lives and what it does\n4. The retention/purge logic that currently handles metrics aggregation\n5. Any existing daily_metrics related code\n\nBe thorough - read full files. Focus on:\n- packages/orchestrator/src/db/ (all files)\n- packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts\n- packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts\n- Any file mentioning daily_metrics or metrics aggregation\n\nReport back the full content of key functions and table schemas.","agentId":"a07ec8fbc6fe597bf","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. **Database Layer Architecture**\n\nThe database layer has been refactored from a single monolithic database (`packages/orchestrator/src/db.ts` - now deleted) to a **multi-tenant per-database architecture** with the following structure:\n\n**File:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/`\n\nKey components:\n- `index.ts` - Barrel export (consolidates all database modules)\n- `schema.ts` - Table definitions and database initialization\n- `_helpers.ts` - Prepared statement caching and row mappers\n- `executions.ts` - Execution CRUD operations\n- `events.ts` - Event and subscription management\n- `triggers.ts` - Trigger definitions and scheduling\n- `personas.ts` - Persona management\n- `tools.ts` - Tool definitions\n- `credentials.ts` - Credential storage\n- `inferenceProfiles.ts` - Model/provider profiles\n\n**Database Structure:**\n- **System database** (`system.db`): Contains tenant registry and system-wide metrics\n- **Per-tenant databases** (`tenants/{hash}.db`): Individual SQLite databases for each project/tenant\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Daily Metrics Table Structure**\n\n**Location:** `packages/orchestrator/src/db/schema.ts` (lines 53-68)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS daily_metrics (\n  date TEXT NOT NULL,\n  total_executions INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  completed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  failed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  total_cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  total_duration_ms INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  PRIMARY KEY (date)\n);\n\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS retention_watermark (\n  key TEXT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT 'executions',\n  last_rowid INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0\n);\n```\n\n**System-level equivalent** (`system_daily_metrics` in `system.db`):\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS system_daily_metrics (\n  date TEXT NOT NULL,\n  total_executions INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  completed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  failed INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  total_cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  total_duration_ms INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  tenant_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  aggregated_at TEXT NOT NULL,\n  PRIMARY KEY (date)\n);\n```\n\nEach tenant's database has its own `daily_metrics` table, which gets aggregated into `system_daily_metrics` daily.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **updateExecution() Function**\n\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/db/executions.ts` (lines 92-120)\n\n```typescript\nexport function updateExecution(db: Database.Database, id: string, updates: Record<string, unknown>): void {\n  const fields: string[] = [];\n  const values: unknown[] = [];\n\n  const columnMap: Record<string, string> = {\n    status: 'status',\n    outputData: 'output_data',\n    claudeSessionId: 'claude_session_id',\n    modelUsed: 'model_used',\n    inputTokens: 'input_tokens',\n    outputTokens: 'output_tokens',\n    costUsd: 'cost_usd',\n    errorMessage: 'error_message',\n    durationMs: 'duration_ms',\n    startedAt: 'started_at',\n    completedAt: 'completed_at',\n  };\n\n  for (const [key, col] of Object.entries(columnMap)) {\n    if (key in updates) {\n      fields.push(`${col} = ?`);\n      values.push(updates[key]);\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (fields.length === 0) return;\n  values.push(id);\n  stmt(db,`UPDATE persona_executions SET ${fields.join(', ')} WHERE id = ?`).run(...values);\n}\n```\n\n**Purpose:** Updates execution records dynamically based on a whitelist of allowed columns. It only updates fields that are explicitly provided in the `updates` object.\n\n**Used by:** `dispatcher.ts` to mark executions as:\n- `running` (lines 440-444)\n- `queued` (lines 184, 194, 235, 452)\n- `completed`/`failed` with full details (line 126)\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Retention and Purge Logic**\n\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/retention.ts`\n\n**Key concepts:**\n\n1. **Daily wall-clock job** (lines 64-100):\n   - Runs once per UTC calendar day\n   - Uses `system_kv` table to persist last run date\n   - Triggered by 60-second polling check\n   - Yields event loop between operations\n\n2. **Three-step per-tenant retention** (lines 232-387):\n   \n   **Step 1: Batch Index Scan** (lines 246-263)\n   - Collects purgeable execution rowids in temp table `_ret_ids`\n   - Processes rows older than retention cutoff with status in ('completed', 'failed', 'cancelled')\n   - Batches collection to avoid holding write lock\n\n   **Step 2: Metrics Aggregation** (lines 269-317)\n   - Uses watermark-based deduplication (tracks `last_rowid`)\n   - Groups executions by `date(created_at)`\n   - Aggregates only never-before-counted rows\n   - Upserts into `daily_metrics` with additive updates:\n\n     ```sql\n     INSERT INTO daily_metrics (date, total_executions, completed, failed, total_cost_usd, total_duration_ms)\n     VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\n     ON CONFLICT(date) DO UPDATE SET\n       total_executions = total_executions + excluded.total_executions,\n       completed = completed + excluded.completed,\n       failed = failed + excluded.failed,\n       total_cost_usd = total_cost_usd + excluded.total_cost_usd,\n       total_duration_ms = total_duration_ms + excluded.total_duration_ms\n     ```\n\n   **Step 3: Deletion** (lines 319-346)\n   - Pre-purge safety check: refuses if deletion would exceed `EXEC_MAX_PURGE_FRACTION` (80%)\n   - Deletes in chunks of 5000 rows with event-loop yields\n\n3. **Event Purge** (lines 348-376):\n   - Deletes non-pending events older than retention cutoff\n   - Safety net: purges stuck events older than 7x retentionDays\n\n4. **System-wide Metrics Aggregation** (lines 150-230):\n   - Map-reduce: reads `daily_metrics` from all tenant databases\n   - Aggregates per-date totals across all tenants\n   - Writes to `system_daily_metrics` wholesale in single transaction\n   - Tracks `tenant_count` per date\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Table Registry (Metrizable Classification)**\n\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/shared/src/tableRegistry.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport const TABLE_REGISTRY: readonly TableRetentionSpec[] = [\n  {\n    lifecycle: 'metrizable',\n    table: 'persona_executions',\n    timestampColumn: 'created_at',\n    metrizableColumns: [\n      { column: 'cost_usd', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n      { column: 'duration_ms', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n      { column: 'input_tokens', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n      { column: 'output_tokens', aggregation: 'SUM' },\n    ],\n    aggregationTarget: 'daily_metrics',\n    maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n  },\n\n  {\n    lifecycle: 'ephemeral',\n    table: 'persona_events',\n    timestampColumn: 'created_at',\n    maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n  },\n  {\n    lifecycle: 'ephemeral',\n    table: 'audit_events',\n    timestampColumn: 'timestamp',\n    minRetentionDays: 90,\n    maxPurgeFraction: 0.8,\n  },\n];\n```\n\nThis is the **single source of truth** for which tables are metrizable vs ephemeral. Helper functions:\n- `getTableSpec(tableName)` - lookup by table name\n- `isMetrizable(spec)` - type guard\n- `isEphemeral(spec)` - type guard\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Tenant Database Manager**\n\n**Location:** `/c/Users/kazda/kiro/personas-cloud/packages/orchestrator/src/tenantDbManager.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport class TenantDbManager {\n  private systemDb: Database.Database;\n  private tenantDbs = new Map<string, CachedDb>();\n  \n  // Layout:\n  // {dataDir}/system.db           — tenant registry\n  // {dataDir}/tenants/{hash}.db   — per-tenant data\n  \n  getTenantDb(projectId: string): Database.Database\n  listTenantIds(): string[]\n  forEachTenant(fn: (db: Database.Database, projectId: string) => void): void\n}\n```\n\nFeatures:\n- **Connection pooling** with idle eviction (10-minute timeout)\n- **Auto-registration** of new tenants in system.db\n- **Safe filenames** via SHA256 hashing of projectId\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Related Code Files**\n\n**Database Initialization:**\n- `schema.ts:initDb()` - Legacy single-db initialization (still used in migrations)\n- `schema.ts:initSystemDb()` - System database\n- `schema.ts:initTenantDb()` - Per-tenant database\n\n**Row Mapper Helpers** (`_helpers.ts`):\n- `stmt(db, sql)` - Prepared statement cache (WeakMap for GC)\n- `createRowMapper<T>(columnMap)` - Generic row mappers replacing per-entity boilerplate\n- `buildWhereClause()` - Dynamic WHERE clause builder\n- `mergeUpdate()` - Update with `updated_at` timestamp\n\n**Execution Schema** (`schema.ts:185-206`):\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS persona_executions (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  project_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',\n  persona_id TEXT NOT NULL,\n  trigger_id TEXT,\n  use_case_id TEXT,\n  status TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'queued' \n    CHECK(status IN ('queued','running','completed','failed','cancelled')),\n  input_data TEXT,\n  output_data TEXT,\n  claude_session_id TEXT,\n  model_used TEXT,\n  input_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  output_tokens INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  cost_usd REAL DEFAULT 0,\n  error_message TEXT,\n  duration_ms INTEGER,\n  retry_of_execution_id TEXT,\n  retry_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,\n  started_at TEXT,\n  completed_at TEXT,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Insights\n\n1. **Metrics aggregation is watermark-based** to ensure idempotency even on crash/restart\n2. **Chunked deletion** with event-loop yields prevents starving concurrent operations\n3. **Additive aggregation** allows safely re-running if previous run partially completed\n4. **Safety caps** (maxPurgeFraction) prevent accidental mass deletion\n5. **Daily job** is wall-clock based (checks every 60s, runs once per UTC calendar day)\n6. **Per-tenant + system aggregation** allows both granular and system-wide metrics\n7. **Registry pattern** makes it easy to add new metrizable tables\n\nAll file paths are absolute from the project root."}],"totalDurationMs":74507,"totalTokens":48128,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3652,"cache_read_input_tokens":41536,"output_tokens":2940,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3652},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
